ept. The majority\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":13448,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/04\/07\/method-ghusl-junub\/","url_meta":{"origin":25583,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ghusl: Performing ritual bath for major impurity","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 7, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: When the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, took a ritual bath for major impurity, he began by washing his hands, then he would perform an ablution as if for prayer. Then, he would put his fingers in the water and wash the roots of his hair\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25576,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/07\/wudu-hadath-junub-loss-mind\/","url_meta":{"origin":25583,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Ablution invalidated by loss of consciousness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 7, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, fainted and then regained consciousness, so he performed a ritual bath for prayer. Then, the Prophet fainted again and regained consciousness, so he performed a ritual bath for prayer. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 418 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Al-Nawawi\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\